primary_diagnosis.description: Major depressive disorder, recurrent, current episode moderate
primary_diagnosis.justification: History confirms prior episodes and the absence of any manic or hypomanic history, supporting the 'recurrent' specifier. The recent initiation of *Sertraline* four weeks ago, coupled with ongoing symptoms and passive ideation, suggests moderate severity and functional impairment, confirming F33.1.
dsm_criteria_met: Meets criteria for Major Depressive Episode (A)
No history of Manic or Hypomanic Episodes (B)
Recurrent status established (Two or more episodes separated by at least two months of remission)

ruled_out.reason: The patient explicitly denies any history of manic or hypomanic episodes, ruling out Bipolar I or Bipolar II Disorder.
